            <p>At Hammer Post, we are constantly evolving to bring our users new features and improve their experience. Below is a list of planned updates and enhancements we aim to introduce in the near future. Stay tuned for these exciting changes!</p>

            <h2>Upcoming Features and Enhancements:</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Advanced Post Editing:</strong> Add formatting options like bold, italics, headings, and bullet points to make posts more engaging.</li>
                <li><strong>Hashtag Support:</strong> Introduce hashtags to help users categorize their posts and discover content more easily.</li>
                <li><strong>Direct Messaging:</strong> Enable private conversations between users to facilitate deeper connections and discussions.</li>
                <li><strong>Multimedia Posts:</strong> Allow users to upload images, videos, and audio files to enhance the visual appeal of their content.</li>
                <li><strong>Dark/Light Mode Toggle:</strong> Provide a switch between dark and light themes for a more personalized browsing experience.</li>
                <li><strong>Post Scheduling:</strong> Enable users to draft posts and schedule them for future publication at a specific time.</li>
                <li><strong>User Groups:</strong> Create community groups where users with similar interests can share posts and engage in focused discussions.</li>
                <li><strong>Content Moderation Tools:</strong> Introduce reporting and moderation features to ensure a safe and respectful environment for all users.</li>
                <li><strong>Post Analytics:</strong> Give users insights into how their posts are performing with metrics such as views, likes, and comments.</li>
                <li><strong>Collaborative Posts:</strong> Allow multiple users to co-author posts, encouraging teamwork and collaboration on large projects or articles.</li>
            </ul>

            <p>We're always open to feedback! If you have any ideas or features you'd like to see on Hammer Post, feel free to <a href="contact.html">contact us</a>. We want to make this platform as user-friendly and engaging as possible.</p>
